---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'SafetyWing in Ecuador', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-safetywing', text: 'Why SafetyWing for Ecuador', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'limitations', text: 'Important Limitations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Who It\'s Best For', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Ecuador', href: '/countries/ecuador/insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing vs IMG', href: '/compare/img-global-vs-safetywing' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Nomad Insurance', coverage: 'Travel medical', price: '$45-70/mo (age 39)' },
  { plan: 'Remote Health', coverage: 'Comprehensive health', price: '$160-220/mo (age 55)' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing Health Insurance in Ecuador"
  description="Guide to SafetyWing insurance for expats in Ecuador. Budget-friendly coverage option."
  headline="SafetyWing in Ecuador"
  subheadline="Budget-friendly coverage option for Ecuador. Best suited for younger expats or as visa requirement solution."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/ecuador-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get SafetyWing"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/safetywing"
>
  <h2 id="overview">SafetyWing in Ecuador</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing offers the most affordable international insurance option for Ecuador. While primarily designed for digital nomads, it can meet visa requirements and provide basic coverage for budget-conscious expats.
  </p>
  <p>
    Ecuador's affordable healthcare costs make SafetyWing's limited coverage less risky than in more expensive countries—though retirees with health concerns should consider more comprehensive options.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$45-70</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Nomad, under 40)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Budget Option</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Most affordable</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Visa Compliant</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Meets requirements</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get SafetyWing Coverage"
    description="Budget-friendly insurance for Ecuador."
    buttonText="Get Covered"
    buttonHref="/providers/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-safetywing">Why SafetyWing for Ecuador</h2>

  <h3>Affordability</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is the most affordable international insurance option—important for budget-conscious expats choosing Ecuador precisely for its low cost of living.
  </p>

  <h3>Visa Compliance</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing meets Ecuador's visa insurance requirements, providing proof of coverage for visa applications.
  </p>

  <h3>Ecuador Context</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing works better in Ecuador than many countries because:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Ecuador's healthcare costs are very low</li>
    <li>Out-of-pocket care is affordable if something isn't covered</li>
    <li>IESS enrollment provides additional safety net</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance (Travel Medical)</h3>
  <p>
    Budget option at ~$45-70/month (varies by age):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>$250,000 maximum coverage</li>
    <li>$250 deductible</li>
    <li>Emergency and hospitalization focus</li>
    <li>30 days home country coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health (Comprehensive)</h3>
  <p>
    Full health insurance at ~$160-220/month (age 55):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Higher coverage limits</li>
    <li>Routine care included</li>
    <li>More appropriate for retirees</li>
    <li>Chronic condition coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Age Considerations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is best for those under 40. Older expats should consider Remote Health or more comprehensive options from IMG, Allianz, or other providers.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance Covers</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Accidents, sudden illness</li>
    <li><strong>Hospitalization:</strong> Inpatient when necessary</li>
    <li><strong>Urgent care:</strong> Non-emergency urgent situations</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation if needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health Adds</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Routine care:</strong> GP visits, checkups</li>
    <li><strong>Preventive:</strong> Vaccinations, screenings</li>
    <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Ongoing management</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Therapy coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="limitations">Important Limitations</h2>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Not comprehensive:</strong> Designed for emergencies</li>
    <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> Not covered</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Limited to 30 days</li>
    <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Not covered (Nomad)</li>
    <li><strong>Age factors:</strong> Premiums increase significantly over 40</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>General Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>No direct billing:</strong> Usually pay upfront, get reimbursed</li>
    <li><strong>Claims process:</strong> Slower than premium insurers</li>
    <li><strong>Customer service:</strong> More limited than Cigna/BUPA</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Who It's Best For</h2>

  <h3>Younger Expats</h3>
  <p>
    Those under 40 seeking budget coverage—SafetyWing works well at this age range.
  </p>

  <h3>Visa Requirement Solution</h3>
  <p>
    Those needing insurance specifically for visa applications at minimal cost.
  </p>

  <h3>Those Combining with IESS</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing + IESS provides reasonable coverage: IESS for local routine care, SafetyWing for emergencies and evacuation.
  </p>

  <h3>Not Ideal For</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Retirees over 55 (consider IMG, Allianz, or BUPA)</li>
    <li>Those with pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Anyone wanting comprehensive coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get SafetyWing for Ecuador"
    description="Budget-friendly coverage option."
    buttonText="Get Covered"
    buttonHref="/providers/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance, not comprehensive health insurance. Understand limitations before relying on it as primary coverage.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
